data.enText: if one thing overlaps another, or the two things overlap , part of one thing covers part of the other
A fish's scales overlap each other.

data.chText: 地板用一张搭着一张的报纸保护着。
data.enText: The floor was protected with overlapping sheets of newspaper.
to make two or more things overlap

data.chText: 你得使这些木片像鱼鳞片似的搭叠起来。
data.enText: You will need to overlap the pieces of wood slightly.
if two events overlap or overlap each other, the second one starts before the first one has finished
to cover part of the same area of interest, knowledge, responsibility, etc.

data.chText: 我们的工作略有重叠，所以有时引起一些困难。
data.enText: Our jobs overlap slightly, which sometimes causes difficulties.

a shared area of interest, knowledge, responsibility, etc.

data.chText: 两门科目之间有相当多的共通之处。
data.enText: There is (a) considerable overlap between the two subjects.
the amount by which one thing covers another thing

data.chText: 每片房瓦上5厘米的重叠度
data.enText: an overlap of 5cm on each roof tile

data.chText: （两事发生的）重叠时间，交接时期

data.enText: There will be an overlap of a week while John teaches Ann the job.

tr: a flap that lies over another part
example: the lap of the shingles should be at least ten inches

tr: the property of partial coincidence in time
a representation of common ground between theories or phenomena
example: there was no overlap between their proposals

value.boxr_value: The verb is pronounced /ˌəʊvə'læp/. The noun is pronounced /'əʊvəlæp/. 动词读作 /ˌəʊvə'læp/。名词读作 /'əʊvəlæp/。

value.def: If one thing overlaps another, or if you overlap them, a part of the first thing occupies the same area as a part of the other thing. You can also say that two things overlap .

example.ex: When the bag is folded flat, the bag bottom overlaps one side of the bag...
example.tran: 袋子平整折起后，底面与一侧交叠。

example.ex: Overlap the slices carefully so there are no gaps...
example.tran: 将切片小心翼翼地搭好，中间不留任何空隙。

example.ex: Use vinyl seam adhesive where vinyls overlap...
example.tran: 塑料布相叠处用塑料封口胶粘起来。

example.ex: The edges must overlap each other or weeds will push through the gaps.
example.tran: 边缘必须互搭在一起，否则杂草会从缝隙中钻出来。

value.def: If one idea or activity overlaps another, or overlaps with another, they involve some of the same subjects, people, or periods of time.

example.ex: Elizabeth met other Oxford intellectuals some of whom overlapped Naomi's world...
example.tran: 伊丽莎白结识了其他一些牛津大学的学者，其中有几位娜奥米也认识。

example.ex: Christian holy week overlaps with the beginning of the Jewish holiday of Passover...
example.tran: 基督教的圣周与犹太教逾越节的头几天重叠。

example.ex: The needs of patients invariably overlap...
example.tran: 病人的需求总有一些是一致的。

example.ex: Their lifespans overlapped by six years.
example.tran: 他们在世的时间有6年是交叉的。

example.ex: ...the overlap between civil and military technology...
example.tran: 民用和军用技术之间的重叠

example.ex: We may begin to discover overlaps.
example.tran: 我们可能开始发现交叉的部分了。

value.tran: （在主题、人物、时间等上）（与…）部分相同，（与…）部分交叉
